model.name: Zarnitsina1996 - Reactions of the Intrinsic Pathway of Blood Coagulation

body.p:
Model listing the reactions of the intrinsic pathway as listed in Zarnitsina1996. Publication model is a spatio-termporal mathematical model of blood coagulation.
Model used as the example of the numerical intrinsic pathway in Braescu et al. (2011).
L. Braescu, M. Leretter, T. George, New direct inhibitors and their computed effect on the dynamics of thrombin formation in blood coagulation, in: T. F. George (Ed.), Computational Studies of New Materials II, World Scientific, 2011, 173â€“190. doi:10.3389/fphys.2012.00266.
